b'\xe2\x80\x9cThis new tower signals our commitment to the city, to the economic development of the area, and to our own prospects for future growth in Milwaukee, and throughout the state.\xe2\x80\x9d - David Casper, U.S. CEO. b'We recently invited students to transform the plywood that covered our main Chicago branch during protests into beautiful works of art that communicate unity and hope. The murals represent the opportunity Chicagoans have to create a more inclusive and just community, together.

The second mural of the project came to life this week, with 15 young artists in the @AfterSchoolMatters program collaborating to create "Bubbling Up and Busting Out\xe2\x80\x9d.

See the murals on display at our main branch on West Monroe starting July 21.'
b'Tap into "no-touch" payment options whenever you see the contactless payment symbol. Pay the safe way with your phone or contactless debit or credit card.'

b'In June 2020, a group of Chicago students transformed the temporary plywood used to cover BMO Harris Bank\xe2\x80\x99s main branch during protests into a work of art that expresses messages of hope and unity, representing the opportunity we all have to create a more inclusive community together.  Click the link in our bio to read more about the mural, which is currently on display at our main branch in downtown Chicago.'

b'We\xe2\x80\x99re raising our voice to denounce racism and intolerance, and declare our support for efforts that are a constructive force for change. Today we\xe2\x80\x99re donating to @naacp_ldf, @eji_org, and the Canadian Anti-Hate Network. View the link in our bio for the full release.'
b'In a laugh, in a smile, in an embrace. This is where Pride lives. It lives in you. It lives in us. #BMOPride'

b'Did you know there was a 667% spike in phishing emails worldwide from the end of February to late March 2020 alone?
